formulae for X†optÄ and k†optÄ in the following table. Theorem 101 proves
that X†optÄ = M(3,s) for s>=81.

The form depends on r = s mod 9 as follows, where s = 9t+r:


              r    k†optÄ   n†optÄ=s-k†optÄ       X†optÄ

